workOrderLines.note: Drove to customer location. Found truck. checked ignition and fuel system. Found truck in need of a tune up. Ordered parts. Parts came in. Returned to customer location with parts . Removed covers next removed regulator hoses,battery and regulator. Removed fittings from old regulator and installed into new regulator. Installed regulator on truck. Connected hoses. Then removed distributor cap,rotor and wires. Engine was hot couldn't removed spark plugs at this time. Installed cap,rotor and wires. Will returned first thing in the morning. Reurned reomed #4 spark plug and had to clean threads up. Installed #4 new plug. Tried to removed plugs from from #1,2 and 3 cylinders. Plugs were starting out hard. stopped removing plugs so that head damsge didn't occur. Talked to customer about removing plugs ans warned them that there could be damage to cylinder head if plug are removed. Customer wanted not to replace spark plugs at this time . Next removed valve cover and gasket. Cleaned valve cover. Installed new gasket. Reinstalled valve cover,and battery. Started truck. Engine still running rough need cylinder 1,2 and 3 spark plugs replaced. Quoted cylinder head replacement.

Customer oked quote. Removed head,exhaust manifold and intake manifold. Cleaned cylinder head surface,intake and exhaust. Installed new cylinder head gasket,cylinder head and torqued head bolts to spec. Then installed timing belt,valve cover,intake and exhaust manifold. Drain engine oil and changed oil filter. Added new oil. Installed distributor ans adjusted timing. Started engine and check for leaks.Found gasket had moved. Removed valve cover and reset gasket. Started engine checked foe leaks. Found none. Let engine run until lifters pumped up. Tested operation. Tested ok. Returned to service .
